Use MAUI's **lifecycle events** (`OnSleep`/`OnResume`) combined with `Preferences` for lightweight storage.

**1. In your page (e.g., `NotePage.xaml.cs`):**

```csharp
public partial class NotePage : ContentPage
{
    private const string DraftKey = "note_draft";

    public NotePage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
    }

    public void SaveDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Set(DraftKey, NoteEditor.Text ?? string.Empty);
    }

    public void RestoreDraft()
    {
        if (Preferences.ContainsKey(DraftKey))
            NoteEditor.Text = Preferences.Get(DraftKey, string.Empty);
    }

    public void ClearDraft()
    {
        Preferences.Remove(DraftKey);
    }

    protected override void OnAppearing()
    {
        base.OnAppearing();
        RestoreDraft();
    }
}
```

**2. In `App.xaml.cs`, hook into the lifecycle:**

```csharp
public partial class App : Application
{
    public App()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        MainPage = new NavigationPage(new NotePage());
    }

    protected override void OnSleep()
    {
        // App going to background — save draft
        if (MainPage is NavigationPage nav &&
            nav.CurrentPage is NotePage notePage)
        {
            notePage.SaveDraft();
        }
    }

    protected override void OnResume()
    {
        // App returning — restore draft
        if (MainPage is NavigationPage nav &&
            nav.CurrentPage is NotePage notePage)
        {
            notePage.RestoreDraft();
        }
    }
}
```

**3. Clear the draft when the user explicitly saves:**

```csharp
private void OnSaveClicked(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    // ... save note to database/file ...
    ClearDraft();
}
```

**Key points:**

- **`OnSleep`** fires when the app is backgrounded or the screen locks — save here.
- **`OnResume`** fires when the app returns to the foreground.
- **`Preferences`** is ideal for small strings; for large text, use `SecureStorage` or write to `FileSystem.AppDataDirectory`.
- Call `ClearDraft()` after a successful save so stale drafts don't reappear.
